{"title":"Rapha for Team Amani","link":"https://theradavist.com/rapha-for-team-amani/","date":1718200254000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3240\" height=\"2160\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?fit=1200,2160&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?w=3240&amp;quality=75 3240w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/image.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Since 2021 the ambition of <a href=\"https://content.rapha.cc/gb/en/story/amani\" target=\"_blank\">Team AMANI</a> has been to climb to the highest peaks of the sport and make East Africa the home of not just endurance runners, but cycling champions as well. Currently plying their craft on the open frontier of gravel racing; these young athletes have the legs and desire to change the landscape…<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"4821\" height=\"3214\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?fit=1200,3214&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?w=4821&amp;quality=75 4821w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/RaphaAmani.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Introducing the Team AMANI collection, inspired by the wildlife of East Africa and Nairobi’s Matatu culture. The collection, which includes jerseys, socks, and accessories, will launch through June 10–14th, find out more and sign up to be notified first at <a href=\"https://content.rapha.cc/gb/en/story/amani\" target=\"_blank\">Rapha</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/rapha-for-team-amani/\">Rapha for Team Amani</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"f3f2f5c69af2d6fc0fb1709d481c624e47f71a63e5f08194b8c5216dcab89c20","category":"Cycling"}